{
  "text": "In part 1 [CITATION_1] , we discussed multimodality imaging of the most common neurodegenerative causes of dementia. In part 2, we build on the reader's knowledge by describing less common causes of degenerative dementia and illustrate the complementary roles of anatomic, metabolic, and sometimes amyloid imaging. Despite the rarity of these conditions, imaging of patients with neurodegenerative disorders is on the rise, and familiarity with the imaging appearances of these atypical causes is increasingly important. ",
